menu "breadboard: bb_log"

config BB_LOG_ROUTES
    bool "Build bb_log HTTP routes (SSE stream + log-level GET/POST)"
    default y
    help
        When enabled, bb_log compiles the routes module that exposes
        GET /api/logs (SSE stream), GET /api/logs/status, GET /api/log/level,
        POST /api/log/level. Adds bb_http, bb_json, and bb_registry to
        bb_log's PRIV_REQUIRES. Disable for headless logging-only consumers.

config BB_LOG_SSE_KEEPALIVE_MS
    int "SSE keepalive interval (ms)"
    default 5000
    range 1000 60000
    depends on BB_LOG_ROUTES
    help
        Interval at which /api/logs SSE emits a comment-frame keepalive
        during silence. Lower values surface dead peers faster (so the
        single SSE slot frees up sooner) but add chunk-write traffic on
        idle connections. Rounded down to the nearest 500ms drain tick.

config BB_LOG_STREAM_AUTOREGISTER
    bool "Auto-init bb_log_stream via bb_registry early tier"
    default y
    help
        When enabled, bb_log_stream_init is automatically invoked by
        bb_registry_init_early() without explicit app_main call.
        Disable to manually call bb_log_stream_init(). Independent of
        CONFIG_BB_LOG_ROUTES (stream capture vs. HTTP routes).

config BB_LOG_STREAM_BUF_BYTES
    int "Stream ringbuffer size (bytes)"
    default 6144
    range 512 65536
    help
        Size of the ringbuffer used to capture log lines for SSE consumers.
        Allocated on heap (SPIRAM-preferred with fallback) only when
        bb_log_stream_init() is called. Default 6144 bytes (6 KB).

config BB_LOG_UDP_SINK
    bool "Mirror log lines to a UDP datagram sink"
    default n
    help
        When enabled, bb_log compiles an optional UDP mirror output. A consumer
        calls bb_log_udp_enable(ip_be, port) at runtime to broadcast every
        formatted log line as a UDP datagram (one per line); a dedicated
        low-priority task owns the socket so sendto never runs inside the IDF
        log mutex. Intended for headless / pre-httpd states (e.g. OTA-only boot
        mode) where the SSE HTTP stream isn't reachable. Default off — the
        machinery is compiled out entirely. NOTE: log lines may carry SSID /
        hostname; enable deliberately.

config BB_LOG_TAG_REGISTRY_MAX
    int "Maximum number of log tag registry entries"
    default 24
    range 8 128
    help
        Maximum number of distinct log tags that can be registered via
        bb_log_tag_register(). Each entry is ~33 bytes BSS. Default 24
        covers typical firmware usage (14-16 tags) with comfortable headroom
        and saves 320 B BSS vs the old hardcoded value of 32. Raise if
        your application registers more than 24 distinct log tags.

config BB_LOG_STREAM_WRITER_QUEUE_LEN
    int "bb_log_stream writer queue depth"
    default 16
    range 4 64
    help
        Number of slots in the bb_log_stream writer queue. Each slot holds
        a log message (~200 B), so this directly sizes internal heap. Lower
        it (e.g. 8) on heap-tight no-PSRAM boards to reclaim ~1.6 KB at the
        cost of dropping log lines under burst logging. Default 16 keeps
        current behavior.

endmenu
